.TH "TAKO" "1" "Jun 2026" "Tako CLI" "Tako CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
tako-history - View deployment history


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBtako history [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
View deployment history stored in the takod mesh.

.PP
This shows all past deployments with their status, timestamp, and services.
You can view details and rollback to any previous deployment.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for history

.PP
\fB-n\fP, \fB--limit\fP=10
	Number of deployments to show

.PP
\fB-s\fP, \fB--server\fP=""
	Server to view history from instead of the full mesh

.PP
\fB--status\fP=""
	Filter by status (success, warmed, failed, rolled_back)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--config\fP=""
	config file (default is ./tako.yaml or ./tako.json)

.PP
\fB-e\fP, \fB--env\fP=""
	environment to deploy (default: production or only environment)

.PP
\fB--host-key-mode\fP=""
	SSH host key verification mode: tofu, strict, ask (default: tofu)

.PP
\fB-v\fP, \fB--verbose\fP[=false]
	verbose output


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBtako(1)\fP
